# SE/30 A/UX 3.0.1 Boot (retail SE floppy).
#
# Intermediate state: the retail boot disk gets the SE/30 past the WGS95
# enabler block (Welcome screen, A/UX Installation "Loading...", then
# "Launching...") before the kernel hits a fatal double bus error at
# virtual $007FEA5D (VBR=$00050000) around instruction 156,973,380.
# After that the CPU halts, the GLU asserts RESET, and the boot sequence
# restarts indefinitely.  See local/gs-docs/notes/09-aux3-retail-se-floppy-dbe.md
# for the full analysis.
#
# The authoritative progress signal is whether the CPU re-enters the ROM
# RAM-sizing entry at $40802A14 more than once.  The breakpoint there
# fires exactly once during a cold boot, and once more per reset cycle.

break $40802A14
run 10000000
info regs

# The crash is observed around ~157 M instructions.  200 M is a
# comfortable budget to reach it without over-running.
run 200000000
info regs

quit
